 pro_sql_13

LIMIT
Using the LIMIT clause in a SELECT statement to limit the number of rows returned from a table.

id - title - release_year - genre
1 - The Shawshank Redemption - 1994 - Drama
2 - The Gosfather - 1972 - Crime
3 - The Godfather: Part II - 1974 - Crime
4 - The Dark Knight - 2008 - Action
5 - 12 Angry Men - 1957 - Drama

Here is example:

SELECT * FROM movies LIMIT 3;

This SELECT statement will return the first 3 rows from the movies table.

id - title - release_year - genre
1 - The Shawshank Redemption - 1994 - Drama
2 - The Godfather - 1972 - Crime
3 - The Godfather: Part II - 1974 - Crime
